post_text:
We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

Timberland Parent and Guardian Update
Re: Collection of Student Property
Timberland Charter Academy Parents and Guardians – Monday May 18, 2020
Michigan Governor Whitmer has extended the Statewide Stay Home, Stay Safe order through Thursday May 28, 2020. In compliance with this request, plans to allow parents, guardians and students access to Timberland campus are postponed. After restrictions are lifted, Timberland Charter Academy will update you on building access to retrieve personal belongs from student classrooms, desk, lockers and to return school materials. Be encouraged and please continue to practice safe health behaviors. We hope to see you all very soon.
text:
Timberland Parent and Guardian Update
Re: Collection of Student Property
Timberland Charter Academy Parents and Guardians – Monday May 18, 2020
Michigan Governor Whitmer has extended the Statewide Stay Home, Stay Safe order through Thursday May 28, 2020. In compliance with this request, plans to allow parents, guardians and students access to Timberland campus are postponed. After restrictions are lifted, Timberland Charter Academy will update you on building access to retrieve personal belongs from student classrooms, desk, lockers and to return school materials. Be encouraged and please continue to practice safe health behaviors. We hope to see you all very soon.

post_text:
How to Draw a Fox (step by step)...

DIRECTIONS

Draw guide lines on paper or fold in half to make creases.
Students follow the tutorial to draw the fox in pencil. (follow pictures)
The fox is traced with black.
The fox is colored very heavily (with crayons, colored pencils, chalk, pastels, oil pastels).
The background is colored.
The black lines are traced again to make them bold, so they really stand out.
Email me a picture of your artwork to 9.lharper@nhaschools.com or bring it in the fall when we return to school!!! Have fun!!
MISS YOU!!!

Our P.E. Teacher Mr. Warren has a message!

Good morning everyone! I hope everybody had a wonderful break! I have a challenge for all my TCA Scholars, here it is!

K-2 morning challenge
10 jumping jacks 10 sit ups 10 push ups before noon 2-3 times a week
3-5 morning challenge
20 jumping jacks 20 sit-ups 20 push-ups before noon 3-4 times a week
6-8 outside challenge: participate in an outdoor activity 3-4 times a week. Activities such as walking , shooting hoops using social distancing, or bike riding.

Please remember to keep social distancing while doing your activities. Stay safe!
